=Typology=

Cadell Last:

Concept Definitions/examples

'''Automated commons Networks''' related to foundational operations of
civilization (i.e. education, health care, transportation,
farming/agriculture, energy) built utilizing the ‘objective
knowledge’ of automated machinery and designed
around principles of universal access, abolition of
property, and phasing out of labour (where contextually
desirable)

'''Collaborative commons Networks''' of social exchange mediated by “offers” and
“demands”(i.e. offer networks) facilitating the
self-organization of good/services built on the
foundation of social trust and reputation as primary
bonding mechanism enabling the general intellect to
disconnect from monetary transactions."

(https://cadelllast.files.wordpress.com/2012/12/last-c-2016-global-commons-in-the-global-brain.pdf)

